pe\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating metadata conditions**\\n\\nI'm considering a potential issue with the metadata. It seems that existing metadata doesn't incorporate TraceWriterAdapter, so I'm wondering if I should include it in the reachability metadata file for the H2 database version 2.1.210. It's important to ensure that all necessary components are accurately reflected, avoiding any gaps that could lead to complications down the line. I'll need to think through the implications of making that addition carefully!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test coverage methods**\\n\\nI’m thinking that the dynamic-access report validates test coverage of active classes based on test execution rather than metadata. However, passing natively does require metadata. It seems existing tests likely depend on `generateMetadata` from outside. I wonder if there's a skill for fixing missing reachability metadata. The user is asking to improve test coverage, not specifically about missing metadata, so maybe I can ignore that skill. I’ll inspect .baseline-stats to know more about coverage, but I don't think it’s necessary. I need to make some edits.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_8iYaH4pWYYGN32UtYawIyjQ1|fc_02174bde2bf242dc0169f4eae2d4388196bc4d3a7835205aec", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.1.210/src/test/java/h2/TraceSystemTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage h2;\n\nimport org.h2.message.Trace;\nimport org.h2.message.TraceSystem;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\n\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class TraceSystemTest {\n    @TempDir\n    Path tempDir;\n\n    @Test\n    void setLevelFileCreatesSlf4jTraceWriterAdapter() {\n        Path traceFile = tempDir.resolve(\"trace-system.trace.db\");\n        TraceSystem traceSystem = new TraceSystem(traceFile.toString());\n\n        traceSystem.setLevelFile(TraceSystem.ADAPTER);\n\n        assertThat(traceSystem.getLevelFile()).isEqualTo(TraceSystem.ADAPTER);\n        assertThat(traceSystem.isEnabled(TraceSystem.ERROR)).isTrue();\n\n        Trace trace = traceSystem.getTrace(\"adapterCoverage\");\n        trace.error(null, \"message routed through the SLF4J trace writer adapter\");\n    }\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.1.210/src/test/java/h2/TraceSystemTest.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage h2;\\n\\nimport org.h2.message.Trace;\\nimport org.h2.message.TraceSystem;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\\n\\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class TraceSystemTest {\\n    @TempDir\\n    Path tempDir;\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void setLevelFileCreatesSlf4jTraceWriterAdapter() {\\n        Path traceFile = tempDir.resolve(\\\"trace-system.trace.db\\\");\\n        TraceSystem traceSystem = new TraceSystem(traceFile.toString());\\n\\n        traceSystem.setLevelFile(TraceSystem.ADAPTER);\\n\\n        assertThat(traceSystem.getLevelFile()).isEqualTo(TraceSystem.ADAPTER);\\n        assertThat(traceSystem.isEnabled(TraceSystem.ERROR)).isTrue();\\n\\n        Trace trace = traceSystem.getTrace(\\\"adapterCoverage\\\");\\n        trace.error(null, \\\"message routed through the SLF4J trace writer adapter\\\");\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1000, "output": 1164, "cacheRead": 26112, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens"